topic.title: Fabric Management

body.p: Fabric management is achieved through the Global Fabric Manager Server (GFMS) provided by PAX firmware. The GFMS runs on each switch in the fabric to allow the connection of one or more external Fabric Managers to any switch. A Fabric Manager communicates through any of the supported MRPC management interfaces (UART, PCIe, I2C, Ethernet, and so on) and the MRPC commands interact with the fabric via the GFMS. Only one Fabric Manager is required to manage the entire fabric, but redundant fabric managers are supported.
The following table lists the MRPC commands used by the external Fabric Manager to manage the PAX Fabric.

entry.p: Set target switch in fabric for MRPC commands
Dump the fabric switch topology information
Dump the fabric GFMS database (DB) information
Bind/unbind a EP function to/from a HVD DSP port
Send EP Management command to EP drives
Retrieve the GFME event data registers
Retrieve communication data from target fabric switch
Endpoint Device CSR and Memory Space Raw Access

body.p: PAX provides a mechanism to notify the fabric management client of a status change anywhere in the fabric. Whenever an event occurs in the fabric, the GFMS will send a notification to the Fabric Manager(s), and the Fabric Manager(s) can retrieve more data from GFMS about the event via MRPC command.
The following table lists a bunch of fabric event code to indicate the fabric events/status.

entry.p: A host link in the Fabric is up
A host link in the Fabric is down
A EP link in the Fabric is up
A EP link in the Fabric is down
A fabric link in the Fabric is up
A fabric link in the Fabric is down
A EP function is bound to one host successfully
A EP function is unbound from one host successfully
Any other event causes the GFMS database changed
An HVD instance is enabled by adding a physical port to the USP
An HVD instance is disabled by removing the USP physical port
A physical port is removed from fabric EP port list
A physical port is added to fabric EP port list
An AER error happens on the EP port
A error happens when peer-to-peer function enable
